                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b W 52/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-07T19:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1922—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 8—12:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. For your information. The following telegram was sent London today: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Please suggest to Kerr advisability of having someone here to watch
                            Western Union interests and work in conjunction with Legation. Foreign
                            Office informs me concession yet to be passed on by the Senate.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
